channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Knockoffs No Longer: Store Brands Get Fancy in a Private-Label Revolution
item.description: Private-label products are gaining in quality and market share in the U.S., following a playbook mastered in Europe.

item.title: The bull market has crushed the shorts. That leaves stocks more vulnerable to bad news, says JPMorgan.
item.description: Short positions in popular assets are at record lows, implying a bet that volatility will stay low.

item.title: Perpetual Sells Bonds, Cuts Cash as Fed Slows Quantitative Tightening
item.description: Australian money manager Perpetual sold off some government bonds and cut its cash holdings in its flagship fixed-income fund following the Federal Re...

item.title: Canada weighs up plans to place fresh tariffs on Chinese electric vehicles
item.description: Justin Trudeau has faced pressure to match the positions of the U.S. and European Union by hiking tariffs on imported Chinese EVs

item.title: Nvidia's Success Is the Stock Market's Problem
item.description: The S&P 500 is soaring to new records driven by Nvidia, while less-important companies fall and remain far below their highs.

item.title: ‘Her world is rocked’: A friend hit the jackpot, but her old friends are abandoning her one by one. Is there a cure for jealousy?
item.description: “Is this jealousy or a change in perceived status that has upended her friendships? Any ideas or cures?”

item.title: Paying Rent With Credit Cards Is (Mostly) a Bad Idea. Here Are the Exceptions.
item.description: Check the math on fees and rewards before charging your rent, tuition, taxes and other bills.

item.title: Britvic rejects $3.9 billion takeover offer from Carlsberg
item.description: The British company which sells J2O said it had rejected Carlsberg’s offer to acquire it for 1,250 pence per share

item.title: Nasdaq, S&P 500 Pull Back From Records
item.description: S&P 500 briefly tops 5500 for the first time, before closing lower, and Wall Street star Nvidia sees its stock fall.

item.title: Actress Sydney Sweeney just bought this $13.5 million breezy retreat in the Florida Keys
item.description: Sydney Sweeney is on a red-hot streak with her real estate purchases, and this one is surrounded by water and palm trees.
